commit.message: Bump PV to 0.3.2.

Don't check action support in sw-notify-send.

Just assume new enough version should be installed already.

Fixes: https://bugs.gentoo.org/show_bug.cgi?id=485898
Bump PV to 0.3.1.
Replace $(basename) with parameter substitution.
Always strip trailing slashes from MOUNTPOINT.
Use public MOUNTPOINT in hooks.
Declare MOUNTPOINT consistently for hooks.

Call 'sw-notify-send --help', tinynotify may not be installed.

It is perfectly legal to have sw-notify-send without tinynotify-send
counterpart installed.
Bump PV to 0.3.
Fix 'make distcheck'.
Use pkg-config to get a sane udev location.
Add a note that polling requires new PATA drivers.
Fix typo.
Differentiate notification actions by umount results.
uam-pumount: handle mountpoint arg as well.
uam-p*mount: when no dev passed, just pass through.
uam-pumount: pass args to pumount.
uam-pmount: support passing pmount options (and label).
Add fmask= to VFAT mountopts.
When not under udev, prepend summary with devname.

Make uam-p*mount match uam-*mount.sh better.

This is necessary for more correct notifications.
Offer 'Remount' action for unmounted event.
Use uam-pumount if available for 'Unmount' notify-action.
Add uam-p*mount to gitignore.
uam-p*mount: unset DEVNAME to ensure non-udev mode.
Add a pumount helper as well.
Whitespace.
uam-pmount: run hooks.
Disable most of the hooks when not running under udev.
Disable cache for uam-pmount by default.
